### Secretaries, general secretaries, and executive directors

Beyond the elected presidents, the daily operations and enduring institutional memory of the AAUP have been maintained by a series of dedicated individuals, whose titles have evolved over time from secretary to general secretary, and most recently, executive director. These are the people who manage the mundane, yet essential, details that keep an organization functioning.

